  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China recently released its 13th Five Year Plan, which will guide China&#8217;s economic, social, and environmental policy through 2020. The plan makes clear that China is integrating climate action into its strategy for economic development. It sets China on course to meet or exceed its international climate commitments, and lays out a strategy for a rebalancing of the economy toward cleaner drivers of growth.</p>

<p>To analyze the key elements of the Five Year Plan in the context of the progress China has achieved and the country&#8217;s remaining challenges, ChinaFAQs organized a press conference call on March 18th.</p>

