  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China&#8217;s 13th Five Year Plan, to be released in the coming days, will provide a blueprint for the country‚Äôs economic, social, and environmental development through 2020. More specific plans for energy and other sectors are expected following the main plan‚Äôs release. The plan comes in the context of China‚Äôs increasing climate action in recent years, with three key trends emerging: China is making progress in rebalancing its economy away from heavy industry toward services, limiting coal use, and expanding its use of non-fossil energy.</p>

