  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>In a move that exceeded expectations, China‚Äôs former Minister in charge of the National Energy Administration, Zhang Guobao, announced yesterday that for the 12th Five Year Plan <a href="http://english.cri.cn/6909/2011/03/04/1461s624079.htm">China would cap total energy use at 4 billion tons coal equivalent (TCE) by 2015</a>.  There had been <a href="http://www.wri.org/stories/2011/03/what-look-chinas-12th-five-year-plan">rumors</a> that China would adopt a total coal cap in the 12th Five Year Plan, but Zhang‚Äôs announcement goes beyond just coal to include all energy sources.</p></div>
